definitions.definition: A supporter of the restoration of the Stuart kings to the thrones of England and Scotland in the late 17th century.
A member of the Syriac Orthodox Church , or historically any miaphysite or monophysite .
A follower of Henry Jacob , a 16th–17th-century Puritan theologian ; an early Congregationalist .

main_definition: ( historical ) A supporter of the restoration of the Stuart kings to the thrones of England and Scotland in the late 17th century. [from 17th c.]
